  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Several studies reported that the use of social media not only helped people to make new contacts but also to develop and strengthen friendships online and in person (e.g., [12,21,24]).",
    "Being able to keep in touch frequently was also important, as one participant reported: 'I do that as soon as I wake up -I check Facebook then when I sit and eat breakfast, I read the news, check Facebook again, at Instagram.",
    "Later, when I get to work, I check Facebook again [to see] if someone has made an update' [29] (p. 297).",
    "Chadwick and Fullwood [22] reported that being connected online in social networks supported relatedness and sharing and 'facilitated maintenance of existing social capital' (p. 57).",
    "Ramsten et al. [29] also reported that social media 'attracted their attention throughout the day."
  ],
